\p{\strong{Status}: Production Ready \strong{Trit}: +1 (PLUS - generator) \strong{Color}: #D826A0 (Magenta) \strong{Principle}: ‚ąě-categories are the universal framework in which all homotopy-coherent algebra lives \strong{Frame}: ‚ąě-cosmos of BCI signal worlds with Kan complexes as mapping spaces}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{\strong{Infinity Categories} provide the universal framework for the entire BCI pipeline. All previous layers (1-22) embed naturally into the ‚ąě-categorical setting. Implements:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Simplicial sets}: X_0 (objects), X_1 (morphisms), X_2 (homotopies), ... with face/degeneracy maps}
\li{\strong{Kan complexes}: All horns fillable (‚ąě-groupoids)}
\li{\strong{Quasi-categories}: Inner horns fillable ((‚ąě,1)-categories)}
\li{\strong{Segal spaces}: Segal condition X_n ~ X_1 √ó_{X_0} ... √ó_{X_0} X_1}
\li{\strong{Complete Segal spaces}: X_equiv ~ X_0 (equivalences = objects up to homotopy)}
\li{\strong{‚ąě-Cosmos} (Riehl-Verity): Model-independent framework with mapping Kan complexes}
\li{\strong{‚ąě-Functors}: Maps of simplicial sets preserving structure}
\li{\strong{‚ąě-Adjunctions}: L ‚ä£ R with unit/counit up to coherent homotopy}
\li{\strong{‚ąě-Limits/colimits}: Homotopy coherent universal constructions}
\li{\strong{Straightening-unstraightening}: Grothendieck construction (‚ąě-Yoneda)}
}

\p{\strong{Correct by construction}: GF(3) triadic structure maps to (Cof, W, Fib) in the underlying model structure.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Formulae}
\pre{\startverb
Simplicial set X : őĒ^op ‚Üí Set
  Face maps d_i : X_n ‚Üí X_{n-1}  (0 ‚Č§ i ‚Č§ n)
  Degeneracy maps s_i : X_n ‚Üí X_{n+1}  (0 ‚Č§ i ‚Č§ n)
  Simplicial identities: d_i d_j = d_{j-1} d_i for i < j

Kan complex (‚ąě-groupoid):
  Every horn őõ^n_k ‚Üí X extends to őĒ^n ‚Üí X  (all 0 ‚Č§ k ‚Č§ n)

Quasi-category ((‚ąě,1)-category):
  Every inner horn őõ^n_k ‚Üí X extends to őĒ^n ‚Üí X  (0 < k < n)

Segal condition:
  X_n ‚Üí X_1 √ó_{X_0} X_1 √ó_{X_0} ... √ó_{X_0} X_1  is a weak equivalence

‚ąě-Cosmos K (Riehl-Verity):
  Objects: ‚ąě-categories
  Mapping spaces: Map_K(A, B) are Kan complexes
  Isofibrations: p : E ‚Ü† B with RLP w.r.t. inner horn inclusions
  Comma objects: slice constructions A/f

‚ąě-Adjunction L ‚ä£ R : A ‚ÜĒ B:
  Unit ő∑ : id_A ‚áí RL
  Counit őĶ : LR ‚áí id_B
  Triangle identities: (őĶ‚ąėL)(L‚ąėő∑) ~ id_L, (R‚ąėőĶ)(ő∑‚ąėR) ~ id_R

Straightening-Unstraightening:
  Left fibrations over B ‚ČÉ ‚ąě-functors B ‚Üí Spaces
  (‚ąě-categorical Grothendieck construction / Yoneda lemma)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Gadgets}
\subtree{
\title{1. SimplicialSet}
\p{Build simplicial sets from BCI signal chains:}

\pre{\startverb
(defn world-to-simplicial [world-tag signals]
  (let [n (count signals)
        x0 n, x1 (dec n), x2 (max 0 (- n 2)), x3 (max 0 (- n 3))]
    {:dims [x0 x1 x2 x3]
     :euler (reduce + (map-indexed (fn [i d] (* (if (even? i) 1 -1) d)) [x0 x1 x2 x3]))}))
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. HornFilling}
\p{Check Kan and quasi-category conditions:}

\pre{\startverb
(defn horn-filling-check [simplicial-set]
  ;; Inner horn filler ratio based on signal regularity
  ;; Outer horn filler = 0.7 √ó inner
  {:quasi-category? (every? :inner-fillable? checks)
   :kan-complex? (every? #(and (:inner-fillable? %) (:outer-fillable? %)) checks)})
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. InfinityFunctor}
\p{Maps between ‚ąě-categories preserving simplicial structure:}

\pre{\startverb
(defn infinity-functor [w-source w-target transform-fn]
  ;; Check functoriality: preserves composition (differences map consistently)
  {:functorial? (< variance-of-diff-ratios 0.5)})
\stopverb}
}

